Deputy Prime Minister Matteo Salvini announced earlier that he had reached an agreement with the EU for Germany, France, Portugal, Luxembourg and Ireland to take in the asylum seekers who have been stranded on the vessel since being rescued at sea last week. 

The migrants had been in two groups in rubber dinghies that had got into trouble after leaving Libya, when they were rescued by fishing boats. 

